WEBVTT

00:10.594 --> 00:12.012
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:12.012 --> 00:13.972
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:13.972 --> 00:16.433
♪ Yo! So, it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.433 --> 00:17.976
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.976 --> 00:21.730
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.730 --> 00:23.232
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.815 --> 00:25.776
♪ Stand up and sing along ♪

00:25.776 --> 00:26.985
♪ All different voices ♪

00:26.985 --> 00:27.903
♪ Everybody now! ♪

00:27.903 --> 00:29.488
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.488 --> 00:31.156
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.323 --> 00:33.325
♪ Yeah, we're livin' in harmony ♪

00:33.325 --> 00:37.120
♪ Our song is much stronger
With every troll singing ♪

00:37.120 --> 00:39.748
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:44.545 --> 00:46.380
LOWNOTE:
I do hereby volunteer

00:46.380 --> 00:49.967
to be the new TrollsTopia
Confetti Inspector.

00:50.342 --> 00:52.636
Signed: Lownote Jones.

00:52.886 --> 00:53.804
Baby.

00:53.804 --> 00:54.972
[ Lownote chuckles ]

00:57.391 --> 00:59.977
‐ And with that,
the final job has been filled,

00:59.977 --> 01:02.813
making the first ever
TrollsTopian Volunteer Sign‐up

01:02.813 --> 01:04.523
a rousing success!

01:06.650 --> 01:07.484
Ahem.

01:07.484 --> 01:09.361
I believe Huzzah's are in order.

01:09.361 --> 01:10.612
EVERYBODY:
Huzzah!

01:10.612 --> 01:11.989
‐ Way to go, friends!

01:11.989 --> 01:15.284
We now have a troll
for every job in TrollsTopia.

01:15.284 --> 01:18.579
Like Holly Darlin',
our new Secretary of Skate!

01:18.579 --> 01:20.706
‐ Ha‐ha, hot dang!

01:20.706 --> 01:24.501
My lifelong dream of skating around
handing out roller skates to everyone

01:24.501 --> 01:26.712
is finally fulfilled! Woo‐‐

01:26.712 --> 01:27.629
‐ Hold that hoo!

01:27.629 --> 01:28.755
[ trolls gasp ]

01:28.922 --> 01:30.382
I don't understand how,

01:30.382 --> 01:33.594
but it looks like Biggie also signed up
for Secretary of Skate.

01:33.760 --> 01:34.803
EVERYBODY:
Huh?

01:34.803 --> 01:35.846
BIGGIE:
Yeah...

01:36.221 --> 01:38.181
I wasn't going to say anything, but...

01:38.682 --> 01:39.600
Uh‐huh.

01:39.766 --> 01:43.103
‐ You mean, we have
two trolls for one job?

01:44.396 --> 01:47.607
Ahem. I believe shocked gasps
are in order.

01:47.733 --> 01:48.984
[ trolls gasp ]

01:49.818 --> 01:51.945
Holly, Biggie, upon further review,

01:51.945 --> 01:55.240
it seems the Secretary of Skate job
was listed twice by mistake.

01:55.824 --> 01:58.702
‐ So, one of you will get to be
Secretary of Skate,

01:58.702 --> 02:02.039
while the other will get the job
that was left off the sign‐up sheet.

02:02.039 --> 02:03.623
‐ Well, which job was left off?

02:04.041 --> 02:06.626
‐ Uh... Vice President
of Telling Little Kids

02:06.626 --> 02:09.129
that They're Too Short
to Ride the Roller Coaster?

02:09.254 --> 02:13.508
‐ So if I wind up Secretary of Skate,
Biggie has to...

02:13.925 --> 02:16.345
[ everybody crying ]

02:16.345 --> 02:19.222
‐ It's for your own safety!

02:19.222 --> 02:22.434
[ everybody crying ]

02:22.768 --> 02:25.187
‐ Poppy! Biggie should be
Secretary of Skate!

02:25.187 --> 02:26.813
‐ No, Holly should be!

02:27.105 --> 02:28.440
‐ I saw this coming.

02:28.440 --> 02:30.692
You both want the other
to have the better job.

02:30.859 --> 02:34.112
So, Dante has proposed
that we settle this with a...

02:34.321 --> 02:35.572
What'd you call it again?

02:35.572 --> 02:36.573
‐ An election.

02:36.782 --> 02:38.075
‐ Yeah. That.

02:38.367 --> 02:40.911
‐ Sorry, what's an "election"?

02:41.119 --> 02:44.373
‐ It's this thing where the people
decide who gets a job,

02:44.373 --> 02:46.750
so the Queen doesn't have
to disappoint anyone!

02:46.750 --> 02:49.503
‐ No, no, Poppy, that's...
that's adorable, but no.

02:49.503 --> 02:52.005
An election is simply
the fairest way to determine

02:52.005 --> 02:54.049
who is best suited for a position.

02:54.216 --> 02:56.635
It's a time‐honored
classical troll custom!

02:56.802 --> 02:58.178
We'll hold a formal debate,

02:58.178 --> 03:00.847
allowing each candidate
to articulate their merits.

03:00.847 --> 03:03.266
Then we let all of TrollsTopia vote.

03:03.517 --> 03:04.726
‐ What do, you guys, say?

03:05.519 --> 03:06.812
BOTH:
Hmm...

03:07.604 --> 03:12.317
‐ Welcome, one and all,
to The Great TrollsTopian Skate Debate!

03:12.317 --> 03:13.860
[ trolls cheering ]

03:14.236 --> 03:15.821
I don't know, Minuet.

03:15.821 --> 03:18.740
I can't bare the thought
of Biggie losing this election

03:18.740 --> 03:22.411
and getting stuck
with that awful roller coaster job.

03:22.661 --> 03:24.162
‐ Yes, it is troubling.

03:24.329 --> 03:29.543
But, Holly, as your campaign manager,
I'll just say: you have my full support.

03:31.128 --> 03:33.380
‐ Biggie, as your campaign manager,

03:33.380 --> 03:37.634
I'll just say: I still don't know
what a debate is, but by glitter!

03:37.634 --> 03:39.594
You're going to look good doing it!

03:42.013 --> 03:42.889
Nailed it!

03:43.974 --> 03:46.017
‐ The first question is for Holly:

03:46.393 --> 03:50.397
what qualities make you a good choice
for Secretary of Skate?

03:50.772 --> 03:51.815
‐ Well...

03:52.399 --> 03:54.651
I'd have to say...

03:57.696 --> 03:58.864
honesty!

03:58.864 --> 04:01.700
Holly Darlin' tells it like it is.

04:01.700 --> 04:03.493
[ trolls cheering ]

04:03.910 --> 04:08.874
For example, some trolls say my opponent
is sweet and hard‐working,

04:08.874 --> 04:11.418
and would make a great Secretary.

04:11.418 --> 04:12.586
Ha‐ha!

04:12.586 --> 04:17.674
But Holly Darling's the only one
with the guts to tell you those trolls...

04:18.300 --> 04:20.552
are absolutely right!

04:21.178 --> 04:22.012
‐ Huh?

04:22.012 --> 04:23.138
EVERYBODY:
Huh?

04:23.513 --> 04:24.973
[ trolls cheering ]

04:25.474 --> 04:26.850
‐ Holly, what are you doing?

04:26.850 --> 04:30.854
‐ Sorry, sugar, but I can't watch you make
them little kids weep on account of me!

04:30.854 --> 04:35.484
So, I'm making sure you win this election,
even if I gotta play dirty...

04:35.942 --> 04:36.777
or clean.

04:36.777 --> 04:39.196
I don't know, this whole thing's
very confusing!

04:39.404 --> 04:41.031
‐ Biggie, same question.

04:41.698 --> 04:44.284
‐ Me? Uh, well...

04:44.743 --> 04:46.620
I'd have to say,

04:46.620 --> 04:51.792
the qualities that would make me
a good Secretary are...

04:53.585 --> 04:56.171
my Southern charm and hospitality!

04:56.671 --> 04:57.506
‐ Wha‐‐?

04:58.006 --> 05:00.801
‐ But aren't those actually
Holly Darling's qualities?

05:01.134 --> 05:02.385
‐ Oh! Are they?

05:02.594 --> 05:04.679
What an embarrassing mistake
I've made!

05:05.180 --> 05:06.848
[ inaudible speaking ]

05:06.848 --> 05:08.892
[ trolls cheering ]

05:08.892 --> 05:10.060
‐ Oh, yeah?

05:10.060 --> 05:13.313
Well, last week, my opponent said
he loves TrollsTopia

05:13.313 --> 05:16.233
'cause he gets to spend
every day with his friends.

05:16.483 --> 05:19.486
But yesterday he said
TrollsTopia symbolizes

05:19.486 --> 05:21.488
the hope of a better tomorrow.

05:21.488 --> 05:25.158
Well, which is it, Biggie?
Friendship or hope?

05:25.992 --> 05:30.205
‐ Well, Holly Darlin' keeps a diary
of everybody's favorite things

05:30.205 --> 05:32.374
so she can get them
thoughtful gifts!

05:32.791 --> 05:33.708
[ Holly gasps ]

05:33.708 --> 05:36.211
‐ I told you that in confidence!

05:36.878 --> 05:39.047
Biggie is fantastic, ya'll!

05:39.047 --> 05:41.007
‐ Holly Darlin' helps everyone!

05:41.007 --> 05:42.968
‐ He sings like an angel!

05:42.968 --> 05:44.594
‐ She smells like pie!

05:44.970 --> 05:45.929
‐ Ohmyguh!

05:45.929 --> 05:48.348
Now they're just resorting
to glitter slinging!

05:48.598 --> 05:51.977
‐ All right, ya'll wanna know
who you should vote for?

05:51.977 --> 05:53.186
Lemme tell ya!

05:53.186 --> 05:56.231
♪

06:01.278 --> 06:05.240
♪ Did y'all know this guy right here's
The MVP of fun? ♪

06:05.240 --> 06:09.327
♪ Holly is so generous
She just can't be outdone ♪

06:09.327 --> 06:11.162
♪ Biggie's brain is extra large ♪

06:11.162 --> 06:13.373
♪ Her intuition's super charged ♪

06:13.373 --> 06:15.125
♪ He's the greatest ever lived ♪

06:15.125 --> 06:16.626
♪ She's got much more to give ♪

06:16.626 --> 06:18.545
♪ He's the best ever ♪

06:18.545 --> 06:20.547
♪ So kind, so clever ♪

06:20.547 --> 06:24.467
♪ Cast your votes for Biggie, yeah! ♪

06:24.467 --> 06:26.595
♪ She's the best ever ♪

06:26.595 --> 06:28.513
♪ Nobody better ♪

06:28.513 --> 06:32.309
♪ Cast your votes for Holly, yeah! ♪

06:32.475 --> 06:35.312
♪ She's the best ever ♪♪

06:38.189 --> 06:39.190
‐ Hmm...

06:39.816 --> 06:41.526
Well... how'd I do?

06:42.569 --> 06:43.612
‐ Not good...

06:44.237 --> 06:45.572
you're ten points ahead.

06:45.906 --> 06:46.823
‐ No!

06:47.157 --> 06:47.991
MINUET:
<i>Yes.</i>

06:48.158 --> 06:50.452
Biggie really nailed us
with those statistics

06:50.452 --> 06:52.329
of how many booboos
you've kissed.

06:53.246 --> 06:54.205
‐ Argh!

06:54.205 --> 06:56.374
But the election is in the morning.

06:56.374 --> 06:59.419
And if TrollsTopia votes for me,
then... then...

06:59.753 --> 07:01.338
[ everybody crying ]

07:01.338 --> 07:04.716
‐ I'm really a very nice troll!

07:04.716 --> 07:07.969
[ everybody crying ]

07:07.969 --> 07:09.471
Don't judge me!

07:09.929 --> 07:12.182
‐ Oh! What am I gonna do?

07:13.058 --> 07:13.892
Hmm?

07:14.934 --> 07:17.270
Anonymous snail mail, for me?

07:18.355 --> 07:19.272
Ah!

07:19.272 --> 07:22.692
Whoever sent this says
they can help me lose the election!

07:22.942 --> 07:23.943
[ Minuet gasps ]

07:23.943 --> 07:26.446
‐ They want me to meet them
at the Black Rock.

07:26.696 --> 07:28.823
"And come alone...

07:29.949 --> 07:34.120
Or bring a buddy,
the more the merrier."

07:40.085 --> 07:42.921
‐ I... I see someone, in the shadows.

07:43.546 --> 07:44.964
‐ Who are you, stranger?

07:45.507 --> 07:46.424
MR. DINKLES:
Mew.

07:47.509 --> 07:50.220
‐ Okay, fine. Don't tell me.
You said you could help?

07:53.515 --> 07:54.349
[ both gasp ]

07:54.349 --> 07:56.267
‐ It's photographs of Biggie.

07:57.185 --> 08:01.231
He has secretly been giving
puppies to babies for years!

08:01.398 --> 08:02.232
‐ Ha‐ha!

08:02.232 --> 08:04.651
When the voters see
this adorable display,

08:04.651 --> 08:06.778
there's no way Biggie can lose!

08:07.070 --> 08:08.780
Thank you, mystery informant.

08:08.780 --> 08:09.948
Whoever you are.

08:11.157 --> 08:12.158
MR. DINKLES:
Mew.

08:12.992 --> 08:15.328
‐ Only 20 minutes before voting starts.

08:15.328 --> 08:18.039
We've gotta get these
to the polling station lickity‐‐

08:18.039 --> 08:18.873
[ both gasp ]

08:18.873 --> 08:20.458
‐ Not so fast!

08:20.625 --> 08:22.252
‐ Yeah, centaur‐troll lady!

08:22.252 --> 08:24.796
Daddy's friend Biggie
does not want those pictures

08:24.796 --> 08:27.757
of his overwhelming
and electable kindness out in the open!

08:27.757 --> 08:28.591
Ya feel me?

08:28.800 --> 08:29.843
‐ Biggie?

08:29.843 --> 08:32.595
But how did you even know
about the pictures?

08:32.846 --> 08:36.266
‐ 'Cause Mr. Dinkles never leaves
our hairpod without leaving a note.

08:36.850 --> 08:41.312
‐ "Went to give Holly
incriminating evidence. BRB."

08:41.938 --> 08:43.189
Oh!

08:43.398 --> 08:46.401
‐ I mean, it's a huge betrayal
and I don't know why he did it,

08:46.401 --> 08:49.612
but I do appreciate the little heart
he used to dot the "I"

08:49.612 --> 08:50.822
in incriminating and‐‐

08:51.448 --> 08:53.283
Hey! Come back here!

08:54.492 --> 08:55.326
‐ Ha!

08:55.910 --> 08:57.037
[ Holly sighs ]

08:57.037 --> 08:58.621
‐ End of the line, Holly!

09:00.331 --> 09:01.166
[ Biggie grunts ]

09:01.332 --> 09:02.167
[ Holly grunts ]

09:02.167 --> 09:03.418
[ Biggie and Holly grunt ]

09:07.797 --> 09:10.467
HOLLY AND BIGGIE:
Oh! Strobe light dance party!

09:10.467 --> 09:13.428
♪

09:19.267 --> 09:20.226
‐ No!

09:21.853 --> 09:22.937
Oh! Uh!

09:23.605 --> 09:24.606
‐ Ha!

09:27.609 --> 09:30.278
DANTE: The vote shall commence
in five minutes!

09:31.404 --> 09:32.530
[ Holly laughing ]

09:32.530 --> 09:33.364
BIGGIE:
<i>Holly!</i>

09:33.364 --> 09:34.532
[ Biggie gasping ]

09:34.532 --> 09:36.076
‐ It's too late, Biggie.

09:36.076 --> 09:37.994
Face it: I win‐‐

09:38.369 --> 09:41.498
by which I mean, I lose...
See? Very confusing!

09:41.498 --> 09:43.291
‐ Holly, I am begging you.

09:43.291 --> 09:45.668
Please, don't leak those photos.

09:45.668 --> 09:48.004
You have to be Secretary of Skate!

09:48.004 --> 09:49.089
‐ No, Biggie.

09:49.255 --> 09:51.716
Sweet as it is,
you ain't gonna help me win

09:51.716 --> 09:53.301
just so you can be nice to me!

09:54.511 --> 09:55.804
‐ "Nice to you"?

09:55.804 --> 09:58.056
I'm not helping you win
to be nice to you.

09:59.015 --> 10:00.850
‐ Wait! You're not...?

10:01.101 --> 10:02.811
Then why...?

10:03.686 --> 10:07.273
‐ Because you're
an incredibly qualified troll

10:07.273 --> 10:08.817
who loves to serve others

10:08.817 --> 10:12.028
and who happens to be
a far better skater than I am.

10:13.029 --> 10:16.699
In other words,
I believe you are the best troll

10:16.699 --> 10:17.742
for the position.

10:18.368 --> 10:21.704
And in the end, isn't that
how everyone should decide

10:21.704 --> 10:22.872
who to vote for?

10:24.707 --> 10:25.583
‐ Oh...

10:26.960 --> 10:29.504
Well, see, now here I am
with my mind all made up

10:29.504 --> 10:33.049
and then you come along and ruin it
by sayin' somethin' beautiful...

10:34.134 --> 10:35.260
Thanks, Biggie.

10:36.636 --> 10:37.554
Here.

10:40.431 --> 10:42.809
‐ Okay, TrollsTopia, let's vote!

10:42.809 --> 10:46.604
[ inaudible speaking ]

10:48.773 --> 10:51.860
‐ Skates for you...
Skates for you...

10:53.486 --> 10:54.612
Ta‐da!

10:55.113 --> 10:58.449
‐ Well, look at you go...
Madame Secretary!

10:58.783 --> 11:01.161
I guess it all turned out best
for everyone, huh?

11:01.161 --> 11:01.995
‐ Yeah!

11:02.745 --> 11:04.122
Everyone but Biggie.

11:04.497 --> 11:05.331
‐ Biggie?

11:05.331 --> 11:06.332
No, wait‐‐

11:06.332 --> 11:07.417
You haven't heard?

11:08.501 --> 11:10.211
Biggie loves his job!

11:10.628 --> 11:12.338
‐ The best part is,

11:12.338 --> 11:16.968
you have something to look forward to
when you are tall enough!

11:16.968 --> 11:18.136
And for now...

11:18.887 --> 11:21.055
how about an ice cream?

11:21.055 --> 11:22.307
TROLLS:
Yeah!

11:23.474 --> 11:24.893
‐ Well, dang ya'll!

11:24.893 --> 11:26.853
He's amazing at this...

11:26.853 --> 11:28.229
who knew?

11:28.229 --> 11:29.522
HOLLY AND POPPY:
Aw!

11:32.734 --> 11:36.029
‐ Yes. Who knew indeed?

11:43.411 --> 11:46.331
POPPY: <i>Welcome, sports fans,</i>
<i>to the playoffs</i>

11:46.331 --> 11:50.293
<i>of one of TrollsTopia's</i>
<i>favorite games: Hug Ball!</i>

11:52.337 --> 11:54.005
TROLLS:
Aw!

11:56.341 --> 11:57.967
‐ Yay!
‐ Woo‐hoo!

11:57.967 --> 12:00.762
‐ And by my side,
with a delightfully folksy take

12:00.762 --> 12:03.598
on the action, it's Holly Darlin'!

12:03.598 --> 12:05.642
‐ Yee‐haw!

12:05.642 --> 12:08.102
We gotta barn burner, Poppy!

12:08.102 --> 12:10.104
Blue Team scored faster
than a grossum

12:10.104 --> 12:12.482
playing table tennis
by the railroad tracks!

12:12.482 --> 12:13.816
‐ That's a saying?

12:13.816 --> 12:16.611
‐ Pff, does a puffalo
drink soup through a straw?

12:16.611 --> 12:17.612
[ Poppy laughing ]

12:17.612 --> 12:19.113
‐ I don't think it does!

12:19.113 --> 12:20.156
‐ Oh, look!

12:20.156 --> 12:22.700
Red Team's about to send out
their biggest star...

12:23.243 --> 12:24.160
<i>Synth!</i>

12:24.160 --> 12:26.704
POPPY: <i>Synth is the troll</i>
<i>everyone wants to see,</i>

12:26.704 --> 12:29.082
<i>due to his very unique set of skills...</i>

12:30.500 --> 12:32.502
POPPY AND HOLLY:
<i>Cheerleading skills!</i>

12:32.502 --> 12:34.420
‐ Woo‐hoo!

12:34.420 --> 12:36.464
[ trolls cheering ]

12:36.464 --> 12:38.883
‐ Ha‐ha,
we can almost touch him!

12:39.008 --> 12:41.469
‐ I can't believe
we got cheer‐side seats!

12:41.803 --> 12:44.389
‐ If you got spirit, lemme hear it!

12:44.389 --> 12:47.558
TROLLS:
Red team! Red team! Yay!

12:47.558 --> 12:50.395
HOLLY: <i>See, leading all them</i>
<i>Techno raves has made Synth</i>

12:50.395 --> 12:52.021
<i>great at workin' a crowd.</i>

12:52.021 --> 12:55.316
And once he gets 'em goin',
well, grab your hairspray

12:55.316 --> 12:57.068
and promote the baby,

12:57.068 --> 12:59.779
'cause the Red Team
plays way better!

12:59.779 --> 13:01.739
‐ Eh, uh...

13:02.198 --> 13:04.951
‐ Make some noise!

13:05.159 --> 13:08.454
[ trolls cheering ]

13:08.454 --> 13:09.789
[ Val grunting ]

13:11.916 --> 13:13.751
‐ Gimme an "R"!
TROLLS: R!

13:13.751 --> 13:15.670
SYNTH: <i>Gimme an "E"!</i>
TROLLS: E!

13:15.670 --> 13:17.171
‐ Add a "D" and you got...

13:17.171 --> 13:20.091
TROLLS:
Red team! Yay!

13:23.886 --> 13:25.596
[ Val grunts ]

13:25.930 --> 13:28.391
HOLLY:
<i>Only 30 seconds left!</i>

13:28.391 --> 13:31.269
But if I know Synth,
well, turn off my music

13:31.269 --> 13:33.646
and say the front yard's
for wrestling,

13:33.646 --> 13:36.316
<i>'cause he's gonna have</i>
<i>a special cheer up his sleeve!</i>

13:36.316 --> 13:37.317
‐ Hey!

13:37.317 --> 13:39.694
When I say "Full", you say "Hearts."

13:39.694 --> 13:41.112
‐ Full!
TROLLS: Hearts!

13:41.112 --> 13:42.739
‐ Full!
TROLLS: Hearts!

13:42.739 --> 13:43.906
‐ Full! Ah!

13:43.906 --> 13:45.241
Aw!

13:45.658 --> 13:46.492
TROLLS:
Huh?

13:48.036 --> 13:49.203
[ Synth gasps ]

13:51.164 --> 13:53.583
POPPY: <i>Uh, looks like</i>
<i>a bumpy cheer broke up</i>

13:53.583 --> 13:55.043
<i>the Red team's mojo.</i>

13:55.043 --> 13:57.545
<i>But I'm sure Synth</i>
<i>can turn it around!</i>

13:58.212 --> 14:01.340
‐ Argh! Bro, we are blowing it!

14:01.340 --> 14:04.093
We gotta pull it together!
Pull it together!

14:05.887 --> 14:07.638
Uh, hmm...

14:08.181 --> 14:10.641
When I say "Hull!", you say "Farts!"

14:10.641 --> 14:12.852
‐ Hull!
TROLLS: Farts?

14:13.061 --> 14:14.062
[ players gasping ]

14:16.147 --> 14:17.648
‐ Uh, hmm, ah...

14:18.107 --> 14:19.442
Ah, we made it worse!

14:19.442 --> 14:22.862
